TY  - JOUR
T1  - Relationships Between Organization Size and Efficiency
AU  - Adler, F. P.
Y1  - 1960/10/01
PY  - 1960
DA  - 1960/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.7.1.80
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.7.1.80
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 80
EP  - 84
VL  - 7
IS  - 1
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - The relation between productivity, efficiency and size of a technical organization as affected by internally generated and circulated paperwork is analyzed. It is shown that there exists an upper bound to total productive output which is independent of the number of employees; and that as the organization size is increased the efficiency generally first rises and then falls off inversely proportionally to the number of employees.
AB  - The relation between productivity, efficiency and size of a technical organization as affected by internally generated and circulated paperwork is analyzed. It is shown that there exists an upper bound to total productive output which is independent of the number of employees; and that as the organization size is increased the efficiency generally first rises and then falls off inversely proportionally to the number of employees.
